Findings: Right internal jugular line terminates at the junction of the brachiocephalic trunk and left port-a-catheter ends at lower SVC/cavoatrial junction. Mild-to-moderate left and minimal right pleural effusion associated with lower lung atelectasis are unchanged since. Mild pulmonary congestion is similar. Heart size is normal. Mediastinal and hilar contours are unchanged.
